This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category as it presents a library for developing high performance parallel programs for compute-intensive tasks. It also mentions the use of cluster computing and scalability with the number of nodes. 

It could also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) category as it applies Blaze to common data mining tasks such as word frequency count, PageRank, k-means, expectation maximization, and k-nearest neighbors. 

The paper also discusses the performance of Blaze compared to other frameworks, indicating a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. 

Finally, the paper discusses the ease of use and development of parallel programs, which could place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category.
